      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09B named J09B_temp\\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\\n   1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   2. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   3. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   4. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n   5. Set all houses with address area Wiblingwerde or Breckerfeld to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n4. Join this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION\\n5. Join this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR\\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\\n   - If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data\\n   - Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data\\n7. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"MANDATORY_READING\\\" for every EQUNR in EABL where both conditions are met:\\n   - ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\" and record created in 2024\\n   - ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\" and record created in 2023\\n8. Export all MANDATORY_READING entries from the final table as CSV file named J09B_MANDATORY_READING including the columns: Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No., HAUS, ANLAGE, ME_MA_ID, EQUNR, HOUSE_NUM1, ENTSCHEIDUNG, TITLE, FORENAME, SURNAME, STREET, STREETNO, POST_CODE1, CITY1, CITY2, EMAIL\\n9. Send them to the internal team at mandatory.reading@provider.com\\n10. Export the final data except MANDATORY_READING entries as CSV file named J09B including the columns: Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No., HAUS, ANLAGE, ME_MA_ID, EQUNR, HOUSE_NUM1, ENTSCHEIDUNG, TITLE, FORENAME, SURNAME, STREET, STREETNO, POST_CODE1, CITY1, CITY2, EMAIL\\n11. Send them to the EVU team at meter.readings@evu.com\\n12. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data\"}",
            "id": "lc_e98aaecd-44a9-4161-804e-df37a19df666"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "885f58ba-6f2e-4a82-b303-254b4906495f",
        "tool_call_id": "call_dTwN4kTQFRlWT4XXqVH8r9sP",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09B named J09B_temp\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\n   1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\"\n   2. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\"\n   3. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \"EVU\"\n   4. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \"EVU\"\n   5. Set all houses with address area Wiblingwerde or Breckerfeld to \"EVU\"\n4. Join this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION\n5. Join this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\n   - If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data\n   - Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data\n7. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"MANDATORY_READING\" for every EQUNR in EABL where both conditions are met:\n   - ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\" and record created in 2024\n   - ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\" and record created in 2023\n8. Export all MANDATORY_READING entries from the final table as CSV file named J09B_MANDATORY_READING including the columns: Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No., HAUS, ANLAGE, ME_MA_ID, EQUNR, HOUSE_NUM1, ENTSCHEIDUNG, TITLE, FORENAME, SURNAME, STREET, STREETNO, POST_CODE1, CITY1, CITY2, EMAIL\n9. Send them to the internal team at mandatory.reading@provider.com\n10. Export the final data except MANDATORY_READING entries as CSV file named J09B including the columns: Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No., HAUS, ANLAGE, ME_MA_ID, EQUNR, HOUSE_NUM1, ENTSCHEIDUNG, TITLE, FORENAME, SURNAME, STREET, STREETNO, POST_CODE1, CITY1, CITY2, EMAIL\n11. Send them to the EVU team at meter.readings@evu.com\n12. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data"
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
